==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[mastodont]]

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1813|1813]], from [[Modern Latin]] genus name [[Mastodon]] ([[wp:1806|1806]]), coined by [[wp:Georges Cuvier|Georges Cuvier]], from {{Gr.}} [[mastos]], "breast" + [[-dont]], "tooth," from the similarity of the [[nipple-like]] [[projection]]s on the [[crown]]s of the [[extinct]] mammal's [[molar]]s.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Extinct elephant-like mammal that [[flourish]]ed worldwide from [[Miocene]] through [[Pleistocene]] times; differs from [[elephant]]s and [[mammoth]]s in the form of the molar teeth.

